  <h2 id="what-to-look-for">What to Look For in Mental Health Coverage</h2>

  <h3>Outpatient Session Limits</h3>
  <p>
    Most plans cap therapy sessions per year:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Basic plans:</strong> 10-20 sessions/year</li>
    <li><strong>Mid-tier plans:</strong> 20-30 sessions/year</li>
    <li><strong>Premium plans:</strong> 30+ sessions or higher limits</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    If you're in regular therapy, calculate whether limits meet your needs.
  </p>

  <h3>Waiting Periods for Pre-Existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    If you have a mental health history (previous therapy, medications, diagnoses), expect:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>12-24 month waiting period before condition is covered</li>
    <li>Possible exclusions for specific conditions</li>
    <li>Full disclosure required on application</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Don't hide history—non-disclosure can void your policy later.
  </p>

  <h3>Telehealth Options</h3>
  <p>
    Telehealth is valuable for mental health care abroad:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to therapists in your language</li>
    <li>Continue with existing providers remotely</li>
    <li>Care in locations without local mental health services</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Verify your plan covers telehealth mental health visits, not just in-person.
  </p>

  <h3>Provider Network</h3>
  <p>
    Mental health provider networks are smaller than general medical:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Check for providers in your specific location</li>
    <li>Verify English-speaking (or your language) availability</li>
    <li>Ask about direct billing vs. reimbursement</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Mental Health Benefits"
    description="See which plans offer the coverage you need."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="finding-care">Finding Mental Health Care Abroad</h2>

  <h3>Using Your Insurance Network</h3>
  <p>
    Start with your insurer's provider directory. Benefits of in-network care:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Direct billing (no upfront payment)</li>
    <li>Pre-approved coverage</li>
    <li>Easier claims process</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Out-of-Network Options</h3>
  <p>
    If network options are limited:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most plans still cover out-of-network with reimbursement</li>
    <li>Pay upfront, submit claims for reimbursement</li>
    <li>May have lower reimbursement rates</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Telehealth Platforms</h3>
  <p>
    Online therapy platforms can supplement insurance:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>BetterHelp, Talkspace, etc. (check if insurance accepted)</li>
    <li>Some insurers have their own telehealth platforms</li>
    <li>Useful when local options are limited</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Language Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    Therapy in your native language is often more effective:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Search specifically for English-speaking (or your language) therapists</li>
    <li>Telehealth expands options beyond local availability</li>
    <li>Expat-focused therapists understand cultural adjustment issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Does travel medical insurance cover mental health?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually no. SafetyWing, World Nomads, and similar travel medical plans typically exclude mental health entirely or only cover acute psychiatric emergencies. For ongoing therapy or psychiatry, you need full international health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I have a pre-existing mental health condition?</h3>
  <p>
    Disclose it on your application. Expect a waiting period (12-24 months) before the condition is covered. During this time, treatment for that specific condition isn't covered, but new mental health issues would be. Some severe conditions may be excluded.
  </p>

  <h3>Are psychiatric medications covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, under prescription drug coverage in full health insurance plans. Verify your specific medications are available in your destination country, as some psychiatric drugs have different names or availability abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I continue seeing my therapist via telehealth?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on your plan and your therapist's licensing. Some insurers cover telehealth sessions with any licensed provider. Others restrict to in-network. Your therapist may have licensing limitations for practicing across borders.
  </p>

  <h3>How many therapy sessions are covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Varies by plan—typically 10-30 sessions per year. Higher-tier plans offer more sessions. Check your specific policy for limits. Some plans have dollar limits instead of session limits.
  </p>

  <h3>Is inpatient psychiatric care covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, in most full health insurance plans. Coverage typically ranges from 30-60 days per year for inpatient mental health treatment. Premium plans may have higher limits.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Coverage details and availability change frequently. We are not insurance brokers or mental health professionals. If you're experiencing a mental health crisis, please contact local emergency services or a crisis helpline.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
